{"id": 243234134, "title": "Everything you need to know as Mother Pride Block Party kicks off in the capital", "text": "One of the country\u2019s biggest pride events, the Mother Pride Block Party, is finally here kicking off at the National Museum of Ireland on Saturday. Mother is hosting two iconic parties at Collins Barracks over Pride weekend, with the brand new Braza Block Party opening up the weekend ahead of Princes Superstar and Cobrah taking to the stage on Saturday to celebrate pride in the capital. On Friday night, the block party kicked off Pride Weekend with co-headliners Pedro Sampaio and Gloria Groove joined by a host of local talent making an unforgettable evening celebrating Brazilian and queer culture. READ MORE: Taylor Swift sends crowd wild at Aviva Stadium show as dancer shouts 'p\u00f3g mo th\u00f3in' READ MORE: Taylor Swift makes one lucky fan's year with huge surprise at Aviva Stadium On Saturday, June 29, from 4pm, to celebrate Pride there will be a truly iconic array of talent including Cobrah, Princess Superstar, Robin S, Sasha Velour and Blu Hydrangea. Joining them on the mainstage across the day of Pride are Mother DJs, Celaviedmai, Sexy Tadhg and Haus of WIG. Other acts appearing across the site include Sing Along Social, Drag Aerobics, Ping Pong Disco, Claire Beck, Conor Behan, Billy Bunzari, Ghostboy, Glamo, Rocky T. Delgado, Roo Honeychild and Ruth Kavanagh. Drag performances across the site are from Anziety, Avatar Guille, Dan the Man Donna Fella, Faux Joli, Mia Gold, Naomi Diamond, Richard Joke, Shaqira Knightly, and Viola Gayvis. Stage times for the Mother Pride Block Party can be found below: Across this iconic city centre site, there will be multiple bars featuring Mother drink sponsors Absolut, Heineken, Whiteclaw and more. Supported by Heineken to minimise our need for single-use plastic, Mother will have reusable cups in use for certain drinks. This year, the world\u2019s leading condom brand Durex, will join onsite to celebrate their My Sex/My Way initiative. The brand is on a mission to empower everybody in Ireland to be their true sexual selves. Come meet, party and celebrate with Durex in Clarke Square all weekend. Mother will also be joined for the weekend by the HSE with their Safer Nightlife programme to reduce harm this summer. \u2018Back of House\u2019 drug checking will be on-site at the Block Party all weekend with the HSE\u2019s Safer Nightlife Programme providing harm reduction outreach teams and \u2018back of house\u2019 drug checking with the aim of reducing drug related harms and increasing understanding of current drug trends. GCN (Ireland\u2019s national LGBTQ+ press will be on-site selling merch. You can pick up tickets here. Join the Irish Mirror\u2019s breaking news service on WhatsApp. Click this link to receive breaking news and the latest headlines direct to your phone. We also treat our community members to special offers, promotions, and adverts from us and our partners. If you don\u2019t like our community, you can check out any time you like. If you\u2019re curious, you can read our Privacy Notice.", "summary": "Cobrah, Princess Superstar, Robin S, Sasha Velour and Blu Hydrangea will all be performing at the Mother Pride Block Party at the National Museum of Ireland on Saturday", "url": "https://www.irishmirror.ie/whats-on/mother-block-party-stage-times-33133046", "image": "https://i2-prod.irishmirror.ie/incoming/article33133054.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_unnamed-9.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 00:55:23", "author": "Cathal Ryan", "authors": ["Cathal Ryan"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ie", "sentiment": 0.523}